<HEADLINE> Portuguese President Visits ICRC Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese President Jorge
Sampaio visited the headquarters of the International Committee of
the Red Cross (ICRC) here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio was received by ICRC President Cornelio Sommaruga. In
his welcoming remarks, the ICRC president praised Portugal's
efforts to promote respect for humanitarian law worldwide,
highlighting the fact that former Portuguese President Mario
Soares had signed the solemn appeal launched on August 12 to mark
the 50th anniversary of the Geneva Conventions.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the recent situation in East Timor, Sommaruga
expressed the ICRC's concern over the tragedy in the area and the
fate of thousands of helpless civilians there exposed to violence
following the referendum on August 30.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Sampaio reiterated his government's support for the
ICRC and underscored the unique nature of the organization's
mandate to assist and protect conflict victims.
</P>
<P>
Ending a three-day visit to Switzerland, the Portuguese
president was on his way back to Lisbon for a parliamentary
meeting on East Timorscheduled on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
