<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Becomes Administrative Member of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has been elected
member of the Administrative Council of the International Postal
Union, the Ministry of Transport and Communications announced here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia was elected along with 39 members on September 7 at
the 22nd general assembly of the union held in Beijing, China, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The membership will last until 2004.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian postal service would draw useful experiences
while being a member in this highest body of the International
Postal Union, the ministry said.  
