<HEADLINE> Most People Trapped in Tunnel Collapse Rescued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Rescue workers have brought
out 17 of the 22 people tonight after they were buried in a
collapsed tunnel in south China for more than 90 hours.
</P>
<P>
The other five are still missing.
</P>
<P>
These people were working in the tunnel in the City of Shaoguan
in Guangdong Province along the Beijing-Zhuhai Expressway which is
under construction, when the tunnel caved in at about two o'clock
on September 6.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 rescue workers were sent to the scene
immediately. They dug a bypass with a diameter of three meters
into the tunnel. They are now still trying to find the missing
workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
