<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Manufacturing Output Continues to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The declining trend in
South Africa's manufacturing output, which started in mid-1997,
has continued so far this year, Statistics South Africa said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The seasonally adjusted manufacturing output in the first seven
months of the year was 2.4 percent lower than the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The output for the three months to July declined by 0.7 percent
compared with the previous three months, it said.
</P>
<P>
Lower output was reported in 13 of the 27 major manufacturing
divisions.
</P>
<P>
However, the output of machinery and textile increased
respectively by 0. 4 and 0.2 percent. 
