<HEADLINE> Cohen to Visit Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 9 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Defense Secretary
William Cohen will visit Russia next week for talks with Russian
Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev on nuclear arms cuts, missile
defense and improving military ties, the Pentagon said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first meeting between the defense chiefs since
June when they met in Helsinki to negotiate participation by
Russian troops in a Kosovo peacekeeping force.
</P>
<P>
Cohen and Sergeyev will discuss improving bilateral
military-to-military ties, which soured this year over NATO's
barbarous bombing in Yugoslavia and concerns in Moscow over U.S.
plans to build an anti-missile defense system.
</P>
<P>
The two military chiefs will also discuss U.S. plans to build
the anti-missile defense system, which Russia says would violate
the 1972 anti-ballistic missile treaty.
</P>
<P>
Because of U.S. recent military actions around the world, the
wary Russian parliament has not yet approved the START-2 strategic
reduction treaty.
</P>
<P>
And Cohen and Sergeyev are also likely to discuss how to make
deep cuts in nuclear weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
