<HEADLINE> Brazilian Judge who Denounced Corruption Murdered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 9 (Xinhua)-- A Brazilian judge who denounced
cases of corruption and disappeared last Friday was found dead in
Concepcion, Paraguay, said authorities Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The body of judge Leopoldino Marques de Amaral, attached to
Matto Grosso state, was carbonized and identified by specialists
from the Secretariat of Public Safety who traveled Wednesday to
Paraguay, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
Marques had been under death threat since having denounced
before Congress that 20 of the 21 members of the Regional Tribunal
of Justice in Matto Grosso were involved in acts of corruption,
such as nepotism and favors to drug traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Paraguayan authorities told their counterparts in Brazil the
finding of the corpse.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Minister of Justice Fose Carlos Dias requested the
Paraguay government allow a joint investigation of the crime.
</P>
