<HEADLINE> U.S. Grants Aid to Rwanda for Debt Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan government
Thursday hailed the United States' aid to the country amounting to
five million U.S. dollars as contribution to Rwanda's Debt Trust
Fund, the Rwandan News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"(This) is yet another concretization of the support of the
U.S. to the reconstruction of our country," Rwandan Minister of
Finance and Economic Planning Donald Kaberuka highlighted during
the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
He said that Rwanda's unsustainable foreign debt burden,
estimated at over 1.2 billion U.S. dollars, or the equivalent of
60 percent of the country's GDP, is a serious brake on the
development effort.
</P>
<P>
"Each year, Rwanda has to pay 30 million U.S. dollars which is
three times higher than the current health expenditure and half
the education budget," Kaberuka said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the U.S. aid will help in servicing multilateral
debt, which accounts for 80 percent of Rwanda's total debt.
</P>
