<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Panama's government is not
to negotiate any treaty with United States to let its military men
carry out exercises here and later invade Colombia, Foreign
Minister Jose Miguel Aleman said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Minister said that Colombia's conflict is its internal
affair and we must give them time to find peace, just as El
Salvador and Guatemala did.
</P>
