<HEADLINE> QPR Meningitis Fears Ease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Medical tests on George
Kulcsar have confirmed that the Queens Park Rangers midfielder is
suffering from the viral strain of meningitis.
</P>
<P>
It is the less deadly form of the disease and most people who
have it make a full recovery.
</P>
<P>
The announcement that it is not the meningococcal variety -- a
potentially fatal strain of bacterial meningitis -- will be a
major boost for both player and club.
</P>
<P>
QPR owner Chris Wright had earlier revealed that three other
players -- Gavin Peacock, Karl Ready and Matthew Rose -- were
under observation in hospital after displaying similar symptoms to
32-year-old Australian Kulcsar.
</P>
<P>
However, tests have now showed that former Chelsea and
Newcastle star Peacock has not been suffering from meningitis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
