<HEADLINE> Manchester United in Silvestre Rush </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer
club Manchester United are trying to push through Mickael
Silvestre's transfer from Inter Milan to enable him to play
against Liverpool on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The French Under-21 defender signed for the club on Friday
after he agreed terms and passed his medical test.
</P>
<P>
The Treble winners are now waiting for his international
clearance from the Italian FA to rubber stamp the deal, which is
reportedly worth 4 million pounds.
</P>
<P>
United chairman Martin Edwards said Friday: "He signed for us
at lunchtime today. He has agreed personal terms, he's passed his
medical and we've completed all the forms.
</P>
<P>
"We have not had international clearance yet, but we hope to
get that from the Italian FA today so that he might be available
for tomorrow."
</P>
<P>
United are anxious to rush through the transfer because they
are desperately short of defensive cover for the Anfield showdown.
</P>
<P>
Gary Neville injured his groin playing for England against
Poland on Wednesday to join Denis Irwin and long-term casualties
Wes Brown, David May and Ronny Johnsen on the sidelines.
</P>
<P>
It would be ironic if Silvestre did make his United debut
against Liverpool after Reds boss Gerard Houllier tried so hard to
sign him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
