<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Arrest 2 Pakistani Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's ruling
Taliban militia have arrested two Pakistani journalists in the
eastern Afghan province of Kunar, the News Network International
(NNI) of Pakistan said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of NNI Peshawar Bureau Salim Safi and another
correspondent of the agency, Mohammad Azam, were taken into
custody in Chaghal Srai in Kunar Province on their way back to
Pakistan on September 7.
</P>
<P>
The two journalists had got visas from the Taliban's consulate
in Peshawar, capital of Pakistan's Northwest Frontier Province and
had visited Afghanistan's northern provinces as part of their
professional duties, an NNI statement said.
</P>
<P>
An NNI spokesman said he didn't know what were the reasons for
the arrests.
</P>
<P>
Various journalist groups have condemned the arrest of
Pakistani correspondents and demanded their immediate release,
said the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
