Federal Parliament, and his party.
</P>
<P>
NPC Chairman Meets AWEU President
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, met here today with Luis Maria de Puig,
president of the Assembly of Western European Union (AWEU).
</P>
<P>
Li said the AWEU has maintained friendly contact with China's
NPC since the early 1980s, and expressed his belief that de Puig's
current visit will make new contributions to this friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that major Western European Union (WEU)
countries are members of the European Union (EU), and said that
with the efforts of both sides, relations between China and the EU
have maintained sound development in recent years.
</P>
<P>
De Puig said members of his delegation represent over 20 WEU
countries, and all harbor the willingness to develop friendship
with China.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Meets European Guests
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian exchanged views on
international and regional security and defense issues here today
with visiting President of Assembly of Western European Union Luis
Maria de Puig.
</P>
<P>
NPC Chairman Meets Azerbaijan Procurator-General
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, met here today with Procurator-General
of Azerbaijan Eldar Hasanov. 
</P>
