<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Rallying Champion Makinen to Stay at Mitsubishi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tommi Makinen
of Finland will stay at Mitsubishi for two more seasons, it was
announced by the team on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Makinen is the only driver to win three rallying titles in a
row. "Mitsubishi is the winning team and I want to remain a part
of that." said the 35-year-old driver.
</P>
<P>
Makinen joined Mitsubishi in 1994. Recent reports said that
Makinen would probably transfer to either Ford or Seat teams.
</P>
<P>
"The next few years will not be easy with so many teams but I
believe we can continue to win," Makinen said in a team statement.
</P>
<P>
The Finn was travelling to China for next week's rally. He said
he wanted to win the events he had not won and became the most
successful rally driver ever.
</P>
<P>
Makinen has scored 18 championship rally wins, five fewer than
the record held by his compatriot Juha Kankkunen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
