<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Leaves for APEC Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee
Hwa left here Friday night for Auckland, New Zealand, to attend
the Seventh Economic Leaders Meeting of the Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) to be held on September 12 and 13.
</P>
<P>
Economic leaders will review progress of APEC's work over the
past 10 years, including various initiatives in promoting trade
and investment liberalization and facilitation and will also
review developments in strengthening the global financial system.
</P>
<P>
At the margins of the meeting, Tung will have bilateral
meetings with the prime minister of Australia and the sultan of
Brunei on September 11 and with the prime ministers of Canada and
Singapore on September 12.
</P>
<P>
They will exchange views on issues of common concern as well as
the bilateral trade and economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Tung will return to Hong Kong on the evening of September 14.
The Hong Kong, China, delegation includes Secretary for Trade and
industry Chau Tak Hay, Director-General of trade Joshua Law,
Deputy Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority Norman
Chan and government economist K. Y. Tang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
