<HEADLINE> Olano Wins Sixth Stage at Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Abraham Olano of Spain took
the sixth stage to strengthen his overall lead at the Tour of
Spain cycling race at Salamanca on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Olano, the defending champion of the race, road a brilliant
time-trial on Friday, clocking 53 minutes and 32 seconds over a
distance of 46.4 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Olano finished 57 seconds ahead second-placed Jan Ullrich of
Germany and extended his overall lead to one minute and 7 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich, the 1997 Tour de France winner, raced strongly over
the first half of the circuit but Olano charged ahead in the
third quarter of the time-trial and had a 43-second advantage over
Ullrich at the 33-km checkpoint. 
</P>
</TEXT>
