<HEADLINE> Macao Teachers Celebrate Own Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,200 teachers in
Macao gathered together Friday night to celebrate the Teachers'
Day.
</P>
<P>
A total of 60 local teachers who have been engaged in education
for 20 years or more were given awards by the Education Department
of the Macao government.
</P>
<P>
"The festival has dual significance as we have the celebration
on the eve of the 100-day countdown to Macao's return to the
motherland," said Vong Fong Va, director of the Chinese Education
Association of Macao.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the motherland has been supporting education in
Macao and exchanges between Macao and the mainland of China are
increasing.
</P>
<P>
Vong encouraged the teachers to keep on acquiring new knowledge
and dedicate themselves to education so as to better live up to
the expectations of the society as well as the parents of students.
</P>
<P>
According to Vong, people of educational circles in Macao set
up a committee in early May to manage a series of celebrations
around Macao's return to the motherland on December 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
