<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Senate Slams MILF's Independence Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Senate President
Blas Ople Friday slammed the attempts of the separatist Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) in Mindanao to model their
independence bid to that of East Timor.
</P>
<P>
"There is no parallel between East Timor and the MILF
movement," Ople said in a press statement, stressing that the MILF
cannot use the East Timor experience as a model for their
independence bid.
</P>
<P>
The statement was in reaction to MILF pronouncements that the
East Timor referendum serves as a good precedent for Muslims
seeking independence to gain sovereignty the peaceful way.
</P>
<P>
A majority of the East Timorese voted for independence from
Indonesia in their August 30 direct ballot sponsored by the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
The ballot gave the East Timorese an opportunity to choose
between autonomy within Indonesia or independence. East Timor was
a former colony of Portugal annexed by Indonesia in 1975.
</P>
<P>
Mindanao and parts of it claimed by the MILF, Ople pointed out,
"are part and parcel of Philippine territory and their status will
never be negotiable."
</P>
<P>
He explained that the referendum provided in the Philippine
Constitution applies only to "application for limited autonomy and
not for total independence." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
