<DOCNO> XIE19990910.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Constitutional Court Overturns Ruling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Against Mandela
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Former South African
President Nelson Mandela was vindicated on Friday by the country's
top court when it reversed an earlier defeat for the government in
a controversial case over rugby.
</P>
<P>
The Constitutional Court overturned the High Court victory of
the South African Rugby Football Union (Sarfu), which had
maintained that Mandela did not give due consideration when he
appointed a commission to investigate the white-dominated sport,
according to a report by the South African Press Association
(SAPA).
</P>
<P>
The Constitutional Court found Pretoria High Court Judge
William de Villiers had erred in finding Mandela at fault in March
last year.
</P>
<P>
De Villiers, who allowed Sarfu to haul Mandela into court, had
said the former president's "performance on the witness stand was
less than satisfactory".
</P>
<P>
The Constitutional Court said that Mandela had not abdicated
his responsibilities when approving the appointment of the
commission of inquiry.
</P>
<P>
"The court finds that evidence does not support the conclusion
that such an abdication took place," SAPA quoted the ruling as
saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
