<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan: From Poor Island to Largest SEZ (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Recently, the State Council has approved the establishment of
an agricultural high-tech zone in Hainan, and more than 200 Taiwan-
based investors have put in a total of 175 million US dollars to
tropical agricultural technological and industrial development.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, the province has ranked first in terms of
economic growth speed among the five special economic zones in
China.
</P>
<P>
Yalong Bay in Sanya, known as "the first bay under the sun."
has been turned into a popular tourist destination handling
millions of visitors every year, said an official of the Hainan
Tourism Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, Hainan has welcomed more than
four million tourists, and seen a 4.6 percent growth for overseas
tourists, said the official.
</P>
<P>
A local official attributed these achievements to the country's
reform and opening policies and joint efforts among government
departments.
</P>
<P>
Before the opening, 2.02 million people, one-third of Hainan's
population, were poverty-stricken. Now, 1.79 million formerly poor
people in the province have got rid of poverty thanks to the
development of local economy and the Hainan's large amount of
poverty-relief fund.
</P>
<P>
The island has three cities and 16 counties, and is the second
largest in China after Taiwan. Before becoming a province, the
island was under the jurisdiction of Guangdong Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
