<HEADLINE> 99 Int'l IT Forum Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The '99 International
Information Technology (IT) Development Forum opened today in this
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of international computer giants including
Microsoft, IBM, SUN, Legend and Founder are attending the event to
discuss crucial issues concerning the development of information
technology.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang is one of the major software production bases in China,
and the local government has issued a series of preferential
policies for IT development.
</P>
<P>
Information technology is set to become one of the three
industrial pillars of the city of Shenyang in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The city is also now holding a concurrent second computer
software festival.  
</P>
</TEXT>
