<HEADLINE> Paper Comments on 100-Day Countdown to Return of Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, the
leading newspaper in China, carries a commentary entitled "Looking
Forward to a Historical Moment" on Saturday to mark the countdown
of 100 days before China resumes sovereignty over Macao on
December 20.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says that the upcoming return of Macao marks a
complete end to foreign colonial rule in China, an important step
toward the country's reunification, and another successful
implementation of the great concept of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
The return of Macao to the motherland is of profound importance
and will strongly push forward the great cause of the peaceful
reunification of the motherland as well as peace and development
in China and the Asia-Pacific Region, the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
The paper goes on to remind readers of Deng Xiaoping, whose
great concept of "one country, two systems" has paved the way for
a solution to the Macao issue and the complete reunification of
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The "one country, two systems" concept has not only provided a
successful example for the peaceful settlement of disputes left
over from history, it is also a creative way of thinking for the
resolution of complicated international disputes, the paper says,
adding that it is also a practical way to solve the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully confident of realizing the complete reunification
of the motherland under the concept of 'one country, two systems,'
" the paper says.
</P>
<P>
Practice shows that the Chinese people are capable of resuming
sovereignty over Macao, and have every confidence in their ability
to maintain long-term stability and development in Macao, the
commentary concludes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
