<HEADLINE> East China City Signs Agreements with Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The city of Fuzhou, capital of
east China's Fujian Province, today signed 13 agricultural
agreements with overseas investors worth a total of 53.1 million U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
A total of 93 agricultural agreements worth 340 million U.S.
dollars now have been reached between the city and overseas
investors at the ongoing Third China Fair for International
Investment and Trade which opened on September 8 in the coastal
city of Xiamen in Fujian.
</P>
<P>
These agreements mainly cover the growing of crops, animal
husbandry, aquatic products, and rural tourism.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector in Fuzhou has been a major target of
overseas investment over the past few years, and the city has
listed 143 agricultural projects open to overseas investment and
cooperation at the fair.  
</P>
</TEXT>
