<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Hydro-Power Station Operational in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A new hydraulic power plant,
the second-largest of its kind in the Tibet Autonomous Region, was
officially put into operation today.
</P>
<P>
The power station, 269 kilometers from the regional capital
Lhasa is at an altitude of 3,800 meters, costs nearly one billion
yuan, and has a generating capacity of 20,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
A special hydraulic power station contractor under the armed
police spent three years to build the plant.
</P>
<P>
The first two generators are currently in the operation, and
the two remaining ones are now being tested prior to installation.
</P>
<P>
The new plant is expected to play a big role in easing the
power shortage in central Tibet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
