<HEADLINE> Macao's Return in Smooth Progress: Chinese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Wang Qiren, director of the
Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch, said here Friday that Macao is in
a sound situation on the way of smooth transition and transfer of
power.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the establishment of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) are being made in an active and
orderly manner and some difficulties in the transition have been
overcome or are being resolved, Wang said in an interview with
some journalists from the state media.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the effective work of the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao SAR since its establishment on May 5, 1998.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal are now actively negotiating on issues
related to the transfer of power and have made encouraging
progress in this regard, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Wang said Macao compatriots have shown increasing enthusiasm in
preparing celebrations of Macao's return and have made plans for
five major celebration events.
</P>
<P>
Wang stressed that Macao's return will further demonstrate that
the "one country, two systems" principle is scientific and correct
and is also the only way to solve the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Lee Teng-hui's claim of statehood for Taiwan goes against the
historical trend and any separatist activities are doomed to
failure, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
