<HEADLINE> Fair for Exports to Taiwan  Opens Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The fourth national commodity
fair for exports to Taiwan is scheduled for April 12-15 next year
at the Fushan International Exhibition Center in the city of
Xiamen in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The fair, approved by China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation, will center on the trade of mechanical and
electrical equipment, according to a spokesman for the fair's
organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
An international computer exhibition will also be held during
the fair.
</P>
<P>
Since it was initiated in 1997, the annual fair has attracted
both domestic and overseas business people, including those from
the United States, Britain, France, Italy, Canada, Singapore and
Japan, and contracts worth 260 million U.S. dollars have been
signed during the event.  
</P>
