<HEADLINE> Petroleum Company Sells Shares on Shenzhen Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A petroleum company based in
Henan Province today sold 806 million yuan worth of shares on the
Shenzhen Securities Exchange at 4.89 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The Zhongyuan Petroleum Company Limited, a subsidiary of China'
s major oil producer, the Zhongyuan Oil Exploration Bureau, is
based in Puyang in central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The company was formed after a restructuring of the former
fourth oil collecting plant and the natural-gas pool of the
Zhongyuan Oil Exploration Bureau, best known as the Zhongyuan
Oilfield.
</P>
<P>
According to the information released by the company, it has
total assets of one billion yuan, a 44.7-sq-km oilfield, and a 24.
7-sq-km gas field with oil and gas reserves of 66.62 million tons
and 19.3 billion cubic meters, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The company has an annual output of 670,000 tons of crude oil
and 800 million cubic meters of natural gas.
</P>
<P>
Funds raised from the sales of the shares will be used to
develop a new oil field, expand natural gas production capacity,
gas processing and other projects, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
