<HEADLINE> HK Official Calls for Joint Efforts in Developing E-Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Secretary for
Information Technology and Broadcasting (ITB) K C Kwong here
Friday called for joint efforts by the academia, the industry and
the government to promote the development of electronic commerce
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Electronic commerce, fueled by the exponential growth in
Internet users worldwide and the advances in Internet computing,
was growing by leaps and bounds, Kwong said, speaking at the
inauguration of new Masters of Science programs on E-Commerce and
Internet Computing launched by the University of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The government fully recognizes the importance of e-commerce
in driving our long-term economic growth," he said, adding "We are
committed to providing a favorable environment for e-commerce to
take hold and flourish in Hong Kong and are embarking on various
initiatives to achieve this challenging goal."
</P>
<P>
For Hong Kong to become a leader in the use of e-commerce, he
said, it is of vital importance to have the people equipped with
the necessary skills.
</P>
<P>
He was pleased to see that all tertiary institutions in the
city had taken up the challenge and were running a wide range of
IT and related programs.
</P>
<P>
In particular, he commended the University of Hong Kong for its
vision in establishing the two masters programs within a
relatively short lead time.
</P>
<P>
"The programs are a timely response to the needs of business as
we press ahead with the launching of e-commerce across the whole
community," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
