<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Azerbaijan Procurator-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li congratulated Hasanov on the signing of an agreement of
cooperation between China's Supreme People's Procuratorate (SPP)
and Azerbaijan's Supreme Procurator's Office, and expressed the
conviction that his current visit will further promote
procuratorial cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hasanov is here to attend the 4th annual meeting of the
International Association of Prosecutors at the invitation of the
SPP. On the major topic being discussed at the ongoing meeting,
anti-corruption, Li said that in the process of the globalization
of the world's economy and the changes of economic modes,
corruption and cheating are unavoidably taking place in China.
</P>
<P>
The fight against such criminal activities is a common task
facing every country, and therefore, all countries, developed and
developing alike, must make joint efforts in this regard, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government, the NPC, and the Chinese procuratorial
organs all attach great importance to this issue, and the fight
against corruption is an important part of China's bid to
establish the rule of law in the country.
</P>
<P>
Hasanov said China has made considerable achievements in the
procuratorial sector, and Azerbaijian hopes to learn from China's
successes in this field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
