<DOCNO> XIE19990910.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Re-Export Value Rises in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's value of re-
export in July this year increased by 5.5 percent over a year
earlier while that of domestic export declined by 10.9 percent,
according to figures released by the Census and Statistics
Department Friday.
</P>
<P>
The department said the value of re-export in the month was 106.
4 billion HK dollars (13.64 billion U.S. dollars) and that of
domestic export 16.2 billion HK dollars (2 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The figures also showed that Hong Kong's value of imports also
rose by 3.7 percent to 127.7 billion HK dollars (16.37 billion U.S.
dollars) compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
A substantial increase of 102 percent was recorded in the value
of re-exports to the Republic of Korea in July, compared with the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Increases were also registered in the value of re-exports to
Singapore, Taiwan, the United Kingdom, the United States, Japan,
the Netherlands, Germany and China's mainland.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first seven months of 1999 with the same period
last year, notable rises in the value of re-exports were achieved
for electrical machinery, apparatus and appliances, office
machines and automatic data processing machines.
</P>
<P>
However, over the same period, decreases in the value of re-
exports were recorded for telecommunications, sound recording and
reproducing apparatus and equipment, footwear, watches and clocks.
</P>
<P>
Comparing July of 1999 with July of 1998, increases were
recorded in the value of imports from Germany, Singapore, the
United Kingdom, Thailand, Malaysia, Taiwan, China's mainland and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the value of imports from Japan and the
Republic of Korea dropped by 5.2 percent and 4.2 percent
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
