<HEADLINE> ADB Closely Monitors Events in East Timor: Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) on Friday said here that it continues to monitor the
situation in East Timor extremely closely.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement released here, ADB said it joins the
international community in expressing its "very deep concern about
the serious security and humanitarian issues" in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Manila-based bank voiced its condemnation of the
widespread violence, particularly in the capital of Dili, which
has followed the holding of a peaceful direct ballot last week.
</P>
<P>
"We stand ready, together with its international development
partners, to provide assistance as soon as possible, under
appropriate circumstances, for the rehabilitation and
reconstruction of East Timor," ADB stressed.
</P>
<P>
Violence began to escalate in East Timor after the United
Nations announced on September 4 that 78.5 percent of the voters
in the August 30 direct ballot rejected autonomy under Indonesia,
paving the way for independence. More than 100 deaths have been
reported following the announcement of the ballot result. 
</P>
