<HEADLINE> Angola Starts Mini-credit Program for Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government Friday
launched a special program for assisting the families living in
poverty, providing women with mini-credits.
</P>
<P>
Angolan First Lady Paula Ana dos Santos inaugurated the
mini-credit program and handed the loans to the people in need
from the the province of Luanda.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony, some 100 women living in poverty accepted the
loans, 100 U.S. dollars for each, delivered by the Angolan
Ministry of Family and Promotion of Women, with an aim to help
them do small business and hence find their means of subsistence.
</P>
<P>
According to the program, those women will have to make a
symbolic restitution of the loans with interests in 20 weeks, as
an essential step for future support.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has learned experience in the mini-credit program
from the non-government organizations which promoted a similar
program two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Those women who used the loans to sell bread, fish, ice cream
and other things could get more loans after making restitution of
the money with interests. 
