<HEADLINE> More Overseas Investment in China's Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- In the first two days of the
ongoing China Investment and Trade Fair in Xiamen City of
southeast China's coastal province of Fujian, China has secured 50
tourism development projects involving a total overseas investment
of 426 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
China is rich in tourism resources, said a tourism official,
noting that revenue from the country's tourism industry has jumped
in rank from the 41st in 1978 to seventh in 1998 in the world.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China received nearly 63.5 million overseas tourists
and recorded a foreign exchange income of 12.6 billion U.S.
dollars. Meanwhile, the country has taken in 239 billion yuan from
694 million domestic tourists.
</P>
<P>
The National Tourism Administration has provided 832 tourism
investment projects in the fields of tourism resource development,
construction of recreational centers and hotel building. The
projects will need a total investment of 95.3 billion yuan.
</P>
</TEXT>
