<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets AWEU President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua)-- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress, met
here today with Luis Maria de Puig, president of the Assembly of
Western European Union (AWEU).
</P>
<P>
Li said the AWEU has maintained friendly contact with China's
NPC since the early 1980s, and expressed his belief that de Puig's
current visit will make new contributions to this friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that major Western European Union (WEU)
countries are members of the European Union (EU), and said that
with the efforts of both sides, relations between China and the EU
and its member countries have maintained sound development in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the facts that political consultations at all
levels have been active, and fruits have been reaped in
cooperation in all fields. Li voiced special appreciation for the
series of measures taken by the EU last year to improve relations
with China.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the EU is an important force on the world stage,
and constitutes an important location in the mutli-polarization
process.
</P>
<P>
China, in pursuit of an independent policy of peace, attaches
great importance to its ties with the EU, and is willing to
continue expanding cooperation in all spheres in a bid to
establish a long-term, stable, and constructive partnership.
</P>
<P>
The world has been far from tranquil since the end of the Cold
War, Li said, stressing that the goal of peace and development is
far from being achieved, and the tasks remain heavy. He further
said he hopes the EU and the WEU will make their due contributions
in this regard.
</P>
<P>
He also said the NPC is willing to develop relations with the
AWEU, the European Parliament, and the EU Commission, to push
forward China's friendly ties with all EU countries.
</P>
<P>
De Puig said members of his delegation represent over 20 WEU
countries, and all harbor the willingness to develop friendship
with China. He agreed with Li's views on multi-polarism, adding it
is beneficial to peace and helpful for maintaining a balance among
international forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
