<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets European Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian exchanged views on international and regional security and
defense issues here today with visiting President of Assembly of
Western European Union Luis Maria de Puig.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
a state councilor, said that China highly valued its relations
with the European Union. China hopes to continue friendly
cooperation in various spheres with EU member countries so as to
establish Sino-EU constructive partnership of long-term stability.
</P>
<P>
On the international situation, Chi said that China stands for
the forming of a multi-polarized world and opposes hegemonism and
power politics. The NATO bombing of the sovereign state of
Yugoslavia under the pretext of protecting human rights, actually
worsened the humanitarian disaster in Kosovo, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chi also stressed that the Taiwan issue is entirely China's
internal affair, which China has the ability to settle on its own,
and in which China strongly opposes any outside interference.
</P>
<P>
Puig said that the current visit by the delegation aims to
enhance understanding of China and exchange views with China on
international and regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Western European Union approves of a multi-polarized world
and favors the guiding role of the United Nations in world affairs,
he said, adding that the union hopes to strengthen dialogue and
cooperation with China in the defense field. 
</P>
