<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Make Progress in Y2K Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua)-- China's police departments
have won their first bout against the Y2K computer bug, a senior
officer with the Ministry of Public Security said here today.
</P>
<P>
Border inspection departments across China have finished 90
percent of their Y2K problem-solving; the country's population
statistics network has completed 80 percent of the work; and the
traffic management system has 60 percent of the job done.
</P>
<P>
Police departments still face some problems involving Y2K,
though the most difficult period is behind them, the officer
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He urged public security bureaus at various levels to work
harder and spend more to eliminate the Y2K problem in time.
</P>
