<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Industrial Production Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production in
India during the first four months of the current fiscal year
which began in April rose by 5.4 percent as against 4.2 percent a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest Index of Industrial Production released
Friday by the Central Statistics Organization, industrial
production recorded a growth of 5.4 percent in July alone as
against 3.4 percent during the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase of industrial production was mainly due to an
impressive 14.3-percent growth in the consumer durable sector
during April-July as against 0.9 percent during the same period
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
