<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Major Iron &AMP; Steel Producer to Issue A Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Shougang Co., Ltd.
, solely launched by China's major iron and steel producer, the
Shougang Corporation, has begun preparations for its initial
public offering.
</P>
<P>
The company announced today that it would issue 350 million A
shares, half of which would be allocated to corporate investors,
while the other half would be offered to the general public
through the Shenzhen Stock Exchange, where the stock would be
listed if the issue is successful.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Shougang Co., Ltd. is the first Chinese company to
issue A shares this way, which was approved by the China
Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) in late July.
</P>
<P>
The company intends to sell its stock for from 4.65 to 5.15
yuan per share, but the final price would be decided based on
investors' reaction.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Shougang Co., Ltd. is a restructured version of the
Shougang Corporation's sintering plant, coking plant, the second
iron plant, the second steel plant, the first, second and third
wire rod plants, and their management and sales departments.
</P>
<P>
The company said it possesses a complete set of internationally
advanced iron and steel equipment and has the capacity to produce
3.8 million tons of iron, 3.4 million tons of steel and 3.2
million tons of wire rods a year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, the company had a total asset worth of 7.9
billion yuan, and a net asset worth of three billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, it reported a turnover of 8.8 billion yuan from its
major business, and a net profit of 840 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
If the issue proves successful, the company would have a total
of 2.31 billion shares, 85 percent of which would be held by the
Shougang Corporation, and the other 15 percent by corporate
investors and the general public.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
