<HEADLINE> Brusnikina Wins Solo in World Cup Synchronized Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Having triumphed in both the
free and technical routines, Olga Brusnikina of Russia succeeded
to win the solo routine in the World Cup synchronized swimming
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The World Championships duet winner scored 98.8 points in the
technical routine and 99.733 in the free routine for a total of 99.
406 to win the solo.
</P>
<P>
France's second ranked Virginie Dedieu came to be the runner-up
with a total of 97.747 and the third place went to Miya Tachibana
of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Comprising solo, duet and team competitions, the event has
attracted a total of about 120 swimmers. 
</P>
