<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Building Materials Industry to Grow Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- China's building materials
industry is expected to score major developments in the next
decade, a senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Lei Qianzhi, vice director of the State Administration of
Building Materials Industry, said that with the country's housing
and infrastructure construction drive, 335 million square meters
of residential buildings will be put up in China's rural areas and
800 million sq m of housing in cities.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, by the year 2005, the length of
highway in China will stretch to 1.45 million kilometers, double
the present length, of which 22,000 kilometers will be expressway,
four times more than now.
</P>
<P>
China has become a major consumer and producer of building
materials. Over the past 20 years, the output value of the country
's building materials industry has maintained an increase rate of
13 percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from traditional key building materials, such as cement,
flat glass and porcelain, new, chemical and decorative materials
will have a wide market potential in China, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
