<HEADLINE> China Boasts 1,001 Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- China has 1,001 stocks listed
on its stock exchanges, while the number of listed companies has
hit 920, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The Changchun Economic and Technology Development Zone
Construction (Group) Co. Ltd. became the 457th A share stock
listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange on September 9.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the Hebei Jinniu Energy Co. Ltd. became the
436th A share stock listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai and Shenzhen bourses also boast 54 B share stocks
each.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here noted that it took only one year for the number
of listed stocks to rise from 900, last September, to over 1,000
now, which means there has been a new stock on the market nearly
every other day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
