<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Securities Firm Approved to Expand Capital Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Securities Company
Limited has been approved by the China Securities Regulatory
Commission (CSRC) to increase its registered capital from 400
million yuan to 850 million yuan, Xinhua learned from the CSRC
today.
</P>
<P>
The company will change its name to Huatai Securities Company
Limited after the expansion of its capital base.
</P>
<P>
The increased capital will come from 22 million yuan in
accumulated funds and 420 million yuan to be raised from its
shareholders.
</P>
<P>
According to the Securities Law that took effect on July 1,
only those companies with more that 500 million registered capital
have the right to underwrite new stocks and operate in the second
market, which usually carries great profits.
</P>
<P>
This has sparked a surge of capital expansion among Chinese
securities companies.
</P>
<P>
Before this, CSRC had authorized seven securities firms,
including Xiangcai, Zhongxin, Guangfa, Xingye and Great Wall to
increase their registered capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
