<HEADLINE> Int'l Association of Prosecutors Concludes Annual Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The International Association
of Prosecutors (IAP) today concluded its five-day annual
conference and general meeting which focused on crimes of fraud
and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Participants called for more frequent exchanges and contact
among prosecutors from all over the world, since the ever-
increasing statistics of fraud and corruption crimes have become a
global issue.
</P>
<P>
Han Zhubin, procurator-general of the Supreme People's
Procuratorate, said that China has drawn up its anti-corruption
and anti-fraud policies based on the realities of its situation,
but it also needs to gain input from others for effective ways to
combating these crimes.
</P>
<P>
China's top leaders have been closely following the meeting in
Beijing. President Jiang Zemin wrote a message to express his warm
welcome to all the delegates. Top legislator Li Peng delivered a
speech at the opening ceremony of the conference and Premier Zhu
Rongji held talks with executive members of the IAP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
