<HEADLINE> Cambodia Steps Up Drafting Intellectual Property Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia is speeding up
drafting intellectual property laws to protect trademarks and
copyrights as well as to attract more investors.
</P>
<P>
"The laws are very important in attracting investors," a
government official said.
</P>
<P>
The draft laws were finished and were being translated from
English into Khmer, so they can hopefully be submitted to the
Council of Ministers this month, according to the Cambodia Daily.
The drafts were amended and approved by the World Intellectual
Property Organization based in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Despite lack of a trademark protection law, the Ministry of
Commerce has managed to issue 12,000 trademarks since 1992 and
enforced international standards of intellectual property law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
