<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 700 Nigerian Youths Infected by AIDS Daily: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 10 (Xinhua) -- About 700 young Nigerians aged
between 10 and 24 are getting infected with the AIDS virus
everyday, a Nigerian scientist has said.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Tony Elujoba, Dean of the Faculty of Pharmacy of Obafemi
Awolowo University, painted this frightening picture in Akure of
Nigeria's southwest Ondo State Thursday when delivering a lecture
on "The Scourge of AIDS" to mark this year's Pharmacy Week
organized by the Pharmaceutical Society of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The professor said that it was almost certain that in the next
three years, a larger percentage of the populace would test HIV
positive, the Guardian newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Elujoba also said that "unless something is done in Nigeria
and other countries to check the menace of AIDS, the next
millennium will herald the era of the world's destruction through
mass dying of the people."
</P>
<P>
Quoting figures from an HIV/AIDS study conducted by his
university, Elujoba said that the scourge of AIDS is gradually
becoming more menacing with the number of the HIV carriers
worldwide expected to rise from 10 million in 1990 to an expected
30 million next year.
</P>
<P>
Declaring the lecture open, Ondo State Commissioner for Health
Rahman Mimiko urged the governments in Africa to make concerted
efforts to curtail the spread of HIV/AIDS on the continent.
</P>
<P>
He said that all levels of government must, as a matter of
urgency, embark on massive enlightenment campaign to educate the
citizens on the menace of the deadly scourge.
</P>
<P>
He regretted that while the AIDS scourge is on the decrease in
developed countries, it is actually increasing in Africa.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that some 1. 7 million young people in Africa
get the deadly virus yearly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
