<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Airlines to Open Route to U.S. Via Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Airlines
(EAL) is negotiating with Ghana Airways to open a flight route to
the United States via Accra, the capital of Ghana, Addis Tribune
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned Ethiopian Airlines has been successful in the
routes Addis-Washington and Addis-New York, launched last year,
and has been forced to increase the availability of the service
due to the increasing demand, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The EAL, which leased two Boeing 767-300 passenger aircraft not
long ago, has opened new airlines and increased its international
flights.
</P>
<P>
During the past one year, the EAL opened new flights to Tel
Aviv of Israel, Beirut of Lebanon and Bahrain while having resumed
its flight to Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The EAL's flight to the United States has also increased to
three times from twice a week one year ago.
</P>
<P>
The EAL, established 52 years ago, currently flies to 47
international destinations, out of which 25 are in Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
