<HEADLINE> China Gets Chairmanship of UPU Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- China was named to the
chairmanship post of the Council of Administration (CA) of the
Universal Postal Union (UPU) for the upcoming five-year term
during today's CA meeting at the ongoing Universal Postal Congress
(UPC).
</P>
<P>
This is the first time China has been offered the position in
the 125-year history of the UPU.
</P>
<P>
Huang Guozhong, from China's State Post Bureau, was elected
chairman of the CA.
</P>
<P>
"This term of CA will make an effort to ensure the strategies
and proposals set by the congress produce tangible results," Huang
said.
</P>
<P>
The CA bears the responsibility of supervising all the
activities of the UPU between the two congresses. It researches
regulations and legislative problems of the UPU, approves the
proposals brought up by the Postal Operations Council (POC) of the
UPU, and is authorized to handle emergency problems that arise
during its term.
</P>
<P>
"China will play a more important role in the UPU in the next
five years," said Liu Liqing, director of the State Post Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Barbados, Morocco, Turkey and Bulgaria were elected vice-
chairmen of the CA. A total of 41 countries were elected as
members of the group.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
