<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Records 2nd Wettest August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong recorded a total
monthly rainfall of 892.0 millimeters in August this year, the
second highest for August in history, the Hong Kong Observatory (
HKO) said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The accumulated rainfall since January 1 was 1676.0 millimeters,
two percent below the normal figure of 1707.4 millimeters for the
same period.
</P>
<P>
August was also cloudier than normal. The mean cloud amount
stood at 80 percent and was the fourth highest for the month.
</P>
<P>
The total bright sunshine duration was only 138.5 hours, the
fifth lowest for August, the HKO said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
