<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kite Fliers Ordered to Keep Away from Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's civil authority
has asked the kite fliers not to play near the Pochentong airport.
</P>
<P>
"The flying of kites near the airport could bring about danger
to the flying of airplanes, particularly during their landing and
taking off time," an official of the Civil Aviation Authority said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Some airlines and pilots have already filed complaints against
kite flying. At least five to six kites are flown near the
Pochentong Airport every day and some of them at the height of 50
to 60 meters, according to the airport authority.
</P>
<P>
In order to avoid unexpected accidents, the Civil Aviation
authority has issued an announcement to the public, especially to
the people living near airports to keep the kites away from the
airports.
</P>
<P>
Kite flying, one of Cambodia's traditional games, has become
more and more popular in the capital as well as in rural areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
