<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Amends Guidelines for External Marriage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Egypt has introduced amendments
to the guidelines for marriage between Egyptian women and
foreigners in an effort to safeguard the rights of the Egyptian
women.
</P>
<P>
Under the new guidelines endorsed by the Justice Ministry on
Thursday, the foreign husbands are obliged to finish the wedding
procedures and sign the marriage contracts in person, the Arabic
Al-Akhbar daily reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The notary public houses must make sure that the bride attends
the wedding ceremony and approves the marriage.
</P>
<P>
The original guidelines allowed foreigners to be deputized when
they complete the necessary legal procedures under the proxy
system.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations also stipulated that the official
registrars should make sure that the age difference between the
would-be spouses does not exceed 14.
</P>
<P>
A foreigner must deposit in the name of his bride-to-be
before marriage 25,000 pounds (7,350 U.S. dollars) in an Egyptian
bank and the money can only be withdrawn by the Egyptian woman.
</P>
<P>
A bridegroom should produce a certificate, documented by the
embassy of his country, on his health, and financial and social
status. Legal action may be taken against the embassy in case the
information is incorrect.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Justice Farouk Seif el-Nasr said on Thursday that
the new guidelines are aimed at securing the rights of the
Egyptians who marry foreigners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
