<HEADLINE> Malaysia Ensures Harmony by Keeping Balanced Economic Status Among Races: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said Friday that the government will continue to
maintain a balance in the economic status of the various races to
ensure continuous harmony in the country.
</P>
<P>
The recent economic crisis has destroyed 30 years of the
government's efforts to achieve a balance in the economic status
of the various races and now a more concerted effort has to be
made to ensure that a balanced status is achieved, he said when
opening the Fourth Bumiputera (aboriginals) Economic Congress
here.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said his government would strive to achieve the
objective of 30 percent distribution of the country's wealth to
Bumiputeras who comprise 60 percent of the country's population.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir called upon Bumiputera entrepreneurs to examine their
shortcomings especially in managing their businesses to continue
to achieve progress, saying such weaknesses had greatly
contributed to the failure of the government's efforts to assist
them.
</P>
<P>
In pursuit of progress in the country, the government also has
to face the challenges of ideas on globalization, Mahathir said.
</P>
<P>
The participants at the two-day congress had a dialogue with
Mahathir, wanting the government to continue to assist Bumiputera
entrepreneurs in facing the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The congress is aimed at assessing the performance and
achievement of Bumiputeras since the New Economic Policy was
introduced in the early 1970's and charting a direction and
drawing up a long-term and short-term action plan for the
development of Bumiputeras. 
</P>
