<HEADLINE> Natural Reserve in Central China Hosts 3,000 Biological Species </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A state-level nature
reserve in central China's Henan Province is now home to over 3,
000 biological species, of which 2,061 are varieties of plants.
</P>
<P>
The Jigong Mountain Natural Reserve, with an area of 3,000
hectares, was established in 1988 with the approval of the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the administrative bureau of the nature reserve has
strengthened cooperation with provincial and state forestry
institutions and introduced over 200 species of plants from many
parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
The reserve's forestry coverage now stands at more than 97
percent, making it a well-known natural treasure in the province.
</P>
</TEXT>
