<HEADLINE> 800-Million-Year Old Riverbed Rock of Yangtze Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Local geologists announced
today that an 800-million-year old riverbed rock from the mighty
Yangtze River has been found at the worksite of the Three Gorges
Hydro-Power Project, in central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The rock was discovered by workers at the country's largest and
most expensive hydraulic project.
</P>
<P>
The find is of great importance to the study of geological
changes and formation of the Three Gorges, the geologists said.
</P>
<P>
The ancient rock, over 200 square meters in size, has an
elevation of -11 meters and is over 70 meters lower than the
surface of the river in the project site, according to the experts.
</P>
</TEXT>
