<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Nigerian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Nigerian newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
New Nigerian:
</P>
<P>
-- The Organization of African Unity (OAU) has ushered in a new
entity, the African Union, for political, economic and military
integration of the continent and the final touches were being made
Thursday night to a declaration that was expected to call for the
creation of the federal entity.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian:
</P>
<P>
-- Business activities at the Apapa Wharf and Tin Can Island
Port in Nigeria's commercial hub Lagos were disrupted Thursday as
intra-union violence among dock workers led to the death of eight
persons.
</P>
<P>
The Post Express:
</P>
<P>
-- Bent on ensuring a reasonable wage bill for public workers,
the Nigerian Labor Congress is set to propose to the Federal
Government a new national minimum wage arrangement.
</P>
<P>
Daily Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi Thursday conferred one of his
country's highest honors on President Olusegun Obasanjo for
Nigeria's show of support and solidarity to Libya "during its most
trying times".
</P>
<P>
This Day:
</P>
<P>
-- Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo enjoined African
leaders at the 4th OAU Special Summit to act decisively to be able
to confront the challenges of the coming millennium in view of the
globalization process and technological development in western
nations. 
</P>
