<HEADLINE> Chinese President Jiang Arrives in Cairns to Continue Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRNS, AUSTRALIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin arrived in Cairns of Queensland State on Friday to
continue his state visit to Australia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was greeted at the airport by Peter Arnison, governor of
the Queensland State, and Peter Beattie, premier of the state. A
brief traditional welcome ceremony by aboriginals was held at the
airport.
</P>
<P>
Jiang came to Cairns, the last leg of his state visit to
Australia, from Sydney.
</P>
<P>
In Sydney, he met leaders of New South Wales State and members
of the Australia-China Business Council, and attended a luncheon
hosted by Australian Prime Minister John Howard with the presence
of premiers of all Australian states and chief ministers of
territories.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is expected to leave here for Auckland of New Zealand on
Saturday to attend the seventh informal leadership meeting of the
Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation forum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
