<HEADLINE> Int'l Finance Corp. Has Shares of Bank of Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- With the approval of the
People's Bank of China, the International Finance Corp., an arm of
the World Bank (WB), purchased 100 million shares of the Bank of
Shanghai, with each share valued at 2.12 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The corporation now accounts for five percent of shares of the
Shanghai bank and one its staff will join the bank's board of
directors, a bank official said today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time the WB has provided funding to China's
banking area, he added.
</P>
<P>
Insiders say that the selling of the shares will help the Bank
of Shanghai to introduce an advanced bank management mechanism,
and to set foot in the international finance market with enhanced
business capability.
</P>
<P>
The International Finance Corp. was set up in 1956 with
shareholders from 174 countries and regions, including China.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Shanghai, originally named Shanghai City United
Bank, was established three years ago and now has 60 billion yuan
in total assets. It has so far had nearly four billion yuan in
profits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
