<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand
sharemarket closed lower here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 3 points lower at 2,124 with a turnover
of 70 million NZ dollars (37 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, AMP was a big loser, falling 54 cents
to 1,861 cents, followed by Telecom down 13 to 835 cents.
</P>
<P>
Sky Network lost 5 cents to 340 cents and Brierley Investments
2 to 47 cents, while Fletcher Building closed unchanged at 265
cents.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey gained 20 cents to 235 cents, Contact Energy
5 to 325 cents, Both Fletcher Energy and Fletcher Forests 2 to 498
and 92 cents respectively, and Fletcher Paper 1 cent to 143 cents.
</P>
</TEXT>
