<HEADLINE> URGENT  Israel Pulls out From 7 percent West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian and Israeli
officials Friday signed the maps outlining the handover of 7
percent more of the West Bank land to the Palestinian civilian
control.
</P>
<P>
Three days ahead of schedule, Israel will withdraw its troops
as of Friday from the 400 square kilometers of the West Bank, a
step to implement the latest Palestinian-Israeli peace accord of
the Sharm el Sheikh Memorandum signed last weekend in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat approved the redeployment
maps delivered to him by the Israeli side. 
</P>
