<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BOC to Unveil Asset Management Corporation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Bank of
China (BOC) revealed today that the bank will soon unveil its
asset management corporation.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President of the BOC Zhao Ange told Xinhua today that the
BOC has formed a leading group for organizing the financial asset
management corporation and another for converting credit rights to
equity.
</P>
<P>
China's four state-owned commercial banks have been approved by
the central government to establish asset management corporations
to handle their non-performing loans. The Cinda Asset Management
Corporation of China Construction Bank was set up in the first
half of this year, while the other three will be established soon.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said that for China's financial industry to enjoy healthy
development, it is vital that the issue of non-performing loans be
solved, and that people's confidence in the country's financial
system be protected.
</P>
<P>
The formation of asset management corporations is the best way
to reach this goal, he said.
</P>
<P>
Specializing in international and foreign exchange businesses,
the BOC has for the 10th straight year been included in Fortune's
top 500 enterprises worldwide, and has been selected by Euromoney
as the best bank in China for four times in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said that this indicates that the BOC's good management
results and solid strength have been fully acknowledged by
international grading institutions. It also demonstrates that the
BOC has become one of the world's largest enterprises and plays an
increasingly important role in China's and even global financial
markets.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, the BOC's total asset reached 2.8 trillion
yuan (360 billion U.S. dollars), with profits hitting 106 billion
yuan (13.6 billion U.S. dollars). The bank's major business
indices continued to grow since the beginning of this year, Zhao
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
