<HEADLINE> China To Hold '99 International Wind Music Art Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 400 musicians from
eight bands both at home and abroad will perform in Beijing and
Dalian during the four-day '99 China Unicom International Wind
Music Art Festival, which starts September 16.
</P>
<P>
The activity is co-sponsored by the local governments of the
two cities and the China Symphony Fund.
</P>
<P>
The bands will be Postmusic of Salzburg from Austria, Derwent
Valley Concert Band from Australia, Silesia Wind Band and the
National Army Concert Band from Poland, the Girls' Marching Band
from Newminster, Germany, the Paul VI High-School Drill Team from
Virginia, U.S., the Shanghai Baoshan Steel Works Group Symphony
Orchestra, and the Dalian Desheng Symphony Orchestra from China.
</P>
<P>
All the bands will also play at the opening ceremony of the
11th Dalian International Fashion Fair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
