<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10th Anniversary of College of Tibetan Medical Sciences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A grand ceremony was held today
in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, to mark the 10th
anniversary of the founding of the Tibet College of Tibetan
Medical Sciences, the only academy in the world that studies and
teaches native Tibetan therapies.
</P>
<P>
After a 10-year growth, the college has formed a complete
system that includes teaching, scientific research, medical
treatment and pharmaceutical services. It now has over 100
teachers and staff and 300 students.
</P>
<P>
The college has trained more than 600 technical personnel for
the autonomous regions of Tibet, Xinjiang Uygur and Inner Mongolia,
and the provinces of Yunnan and Gansu over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
Tibetan medicine, which has a history of over 1,000 years, has
witnessed rapid development since the 1980s. Its practitioners say
it is extremely effective in treating many chronic diseases,
including cancer and strokes, and is favored by the Tibetan people
today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
