<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Declare Year 2000 as Ecotourism Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has decided to
declare year 2000 as "Year of Ecotourism" in a bid to tap the
potential of the fast growing segment in the tourism sector, the
Ministry of Tourism said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A ministry spokesman said the government is formulating a
National Ecotourism Policy Plan to promote Sri Lanka as an unique
ecotourism destination.
</P>
<P>
The decision follows representations by the Ecotourism Society
of Sri Lanka, he said, adding that Sri Lanka will capitalize on
the United Nations' move to declare year 2002 as the "Year of
Ecotourism" worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka could be successfully marketed to lure those who
prefer to divert from the sun, sea and beach vacations, said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ecotourism Society, ecotourism is responsible
travel to natural areas which conserves the environment and
improves the welfare of the local people.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka, the Pearl of the Indian Ocean, is blessed with
resource base for ecotourism, ranging from the highest level of
bio-diversity per square kilometer of surface in Asia to historic
and cultural sites including a number of world heritage sites.
</P>
</TEXT>
