<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily published
an editorial today which said that although the nationwide
campaign against Falun Gong, an outlawed cult, has been successful,
governments at all levels should be alert to some Falun Gong
followers who refuse to abandon illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
"We should not expect a rainstorm to wash away all withered
leaves," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
It cited a recent case from the Beijing Public Security Bureau,
in which 19 Falun Gong practitioners were apprehended by police
for gathering illegally.
</P>
<P>
The editorial called for vigilance against those die-hard Falun
Gong members, saying that they still constitute a threat to social
stability and people's thinking if not properly handled.
</P>
<P>
"Stability is the supreme interest of both the state and the
people, especially before the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic and the return of Macao," it says. "Any
attempt to create chaos or disrupt stability goes against the will
of the people and is doomed to fail."  
