<HEADLINE> Myanmar-Japan Bilateral Trade Increases Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The bilateral trade between
Myanmar and Japan amounted to 405.64 million U.S. dollars in the
fiscal 1998-99 which ended in March, up 0.5 percent compared with
that of the previous fiscal year which was 403.56 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The official Economic Indicators said in its latest issue that
of the total, Myanmar's import from Japan was valued at 357.23
million dollars, 1.7 percent less than the figure recorded in the
previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's export to Japan in the fiscal year stood at 48.41
million dollars, increasing 21 percent over the previous fiscal
year which was 40 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Japan is Myanmar's third major trading partner after the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations and China.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, during the five-year period from April 1994 to April
1999, Myanmar absorbed investments amounting to 123 million
dollars from Japan in 16 projects, accounting for 2.18 percent of
the total foreign investments during the period which was 5.64
billion dollars. 
</P>
