<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Y2K Incidents Reported in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- No major Y2K-induced incidents
were reported in Macao on September 9, a high risky date of
computer millennium bug, according to the Y2K information center
of Macao Friday.
</P>
<P>
The center received no telephone call to seek help involving
Y2K problems by any enterprise Thursday thanks to the full
preparation made by key institutions, including departments of
telecommunications, water and power supply and banks.
</P>
<P>
To ensure a timely resolution of Y2K incidents that possibly
took place, relevant public institutions and banks had their staff
on duty from Wednesday evening to Thursday midnight.
</P>
<P>
The staff of public institutions were also required to start
work earlier Thursday to check their computers before the office
hours.
</P>
<P>
Macao banks said everything remained normal Thursday, without
any increase of drawing money for fear of Y2K problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
