<HEADLINE> 8 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Eight members of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed and five Turkish military
personnel wounded in an armed clash in eastern Turkey on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The armed clash broke out when the security forces were making
search for the PKK rebels in the countryside of Agri province, the
semi-official Anatolia news agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The security forces killed eight PKK militants including two
women, but five soldiers of the security forces were wounded in
the armed clash, added the agency.
</P>
<P>
The injured was taken to a hospital for medical treatment, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Imprisoned PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan ordered an end to the
armed struggle against the Turkish government and people after he
had been sentenced to death for treason.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government has refused to negotiate with the PKK
who has been fighting a 15-year-old guerrilla war for an
independent state in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The conflicts between the Turkish government and the PKK have
claimed over 37,000 lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
