<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Completes Landing Exercises (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South and East China Sea Coasts, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The
People's Liberation Army's (PLA) naval, air, and ground forces
held large joint landing exercises earlier this month in coastal
parts of Zhejiang Province and the southern part of Guangdong
Provcince.
</P>
<P>
The troops participating were from the Nanjing and Guangzhou
Military Area Commands, the Second Artillery Corps, and reserves.
</P>
<P>
The successful exercise showed how the PLA has improved its
joint military combat capacity and the success of its
modernization drive and how it is ready to defend the country's
sovereignty, territorial integrity, and to crack down on any
separatist acts.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
was present at the exercises and conveyed the greetings of
President Jiang Zemin and the Central Military Commission to the
PLA and militia members participating in the exercises.
</P>
<P>
The PLA did a landing exercise armed with high-tech weapons on
the East China Sea, where the Opium War took place in the last
century. Officers and enlisted personnel moved heavy weapons and
swiftly completed the formation of combat groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
