<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Completes Landing Exercises (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The military exercise provided a spectacular sight of a straits-
crossing and landing operation by Chinese forces armed with high-
tech weapons.
</P>
<P>
The new equipment doubled the might of land, naval and air
forces, military analysts said, and advanced naval vessels,
aircraft, and electronic warfare technology gave the PLA total of
the sea and air and electronic communications mastery.
</P>
<P>
Landing ships, hovercraft, helicopters, and other modern forms
of transportation gave the attack invincibility and a computerized
artillery system gave more flexibility, they said. An automated
command system connecting troops and headquarters greatly
increased the efficiency when combined with pilotless scouts and a
comprehensive intelligence system in the war zone, they said.
</P>
<P>
Both Tao Bojun, the chief of staff, and Liu Shutian, the
political commissar, of the Guangzhou Military Zone, told Xinhua
that the land, naval, and air forces have increased research,
training reforms, technology, and proficiency of officers and
enlisted personnel to defend the unity of the Chinese nation, in
recent years.
</P>
