place the country in front of a major financial crisis, commented
the local Nine O'clock daily on Thursday citing a recent report on
Romania made by the international rating agency Moody's.
</P>
<P>
The rating for Romania - B3 for the debt in foreign currency,
Caa1 for banking deposits in foreign currency and Caa1 for the
debt in home currency, are accompanied by a perspective of steady
rating, because they already express "a very big probability of an
incapacity of payment," Moody's said.  (Romania-IMF)
