<HEADLINE> Canada Announces Aid to East Timor People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Canada announced 420,000
Canadian dollars (about 282,198 U.S. dollars) in aid Thursday to
help those displaced people in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of people have fled their homes to escape
the wave of violence in East Timor, and they must be provided with
basic supplies, said Canadian Minister for International
Cooperation Maria Minna.
</P>
<P>
She said the money will be used to buy survival kits for about
25,000 homeless people, each containing a storage drum for water,
cooking utensils, tarps for emergency shelter, blankets and
clothing.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of people have been killed in violence since the
announcement of the direct autonomy ballot in East Timor on
September 4. The Indonesian army Tuesday declared a state of
emergency in East Timor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
