<DOCNO> XIE19990910.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fresh Water Species Drastically Diminishing: WWF Report Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Over 51 percent of all
fresh water species of fish throughout the world are drastically
diminishing, a report issued by World Wildlife Fund (WWF), the
international environment network, said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It is a matter of great urgency and a call to action to do all
that is possible to prevent the loss of these species when the
world is about to enter the 21st century, said Claude Martin,
general secretary of the WWF.
</P>
<P>
He said, "the reduction seen in fresh water species is
particularly worrisome as an indicator of the degree of
deterioration in the quality of rivers, lakes and wet lands."
</P>
<P>
Among the fresh water species, the amphibians have been
seriously devastated, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In Australia, Panama and the United States, about 20 species of
frogs have perished due to an unknown fungus caused by pollution,
the report says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990910.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> University Conflict Affects Mexican Educational System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The stopping of
activities in Mexico's Autonomous National University (UNAM) --
the largest on the continent -- has affected practically the
country's whole system of higher education.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of the National Association of Universities
and Institutions of Superior Education (ANNUISE), Julio Rubio,
said on Thursday that cooperation and exchanges among different
universities and institutions have been suspended for 140 days.
</P>
<P>
The stopping of activities was caused by a strike that broke
out last April on campus as students opposed the increase of
schooling fees by the university authorities.
</P>
<P>
In the last few days, UNAM's authorities put conditions for
negotiation to settle the conflict, which however distanced the
possibility of a solution.
</P>
<P>
Besides the undergraduate students body, there are also
hundreds of students and teachers from across the country taking
postgraduate courses at UNAM who have been unable to get ahead in
their work.
</P>
<P>
But when the stoppage is over, there is hope to find new
mechanisms to make up what is lost, Rubio said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
