<HEADLINE> Mexico Promises not to Use Force to Solve Chiapas Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Mexican Interior
Secretary Diodoro Carrasco promised Thursday not to use force to
solve the conflict in the southern state of Chiapas.
</P>
<P>
Carrasco said the government rejects any force to solve the
conflict there that broke out on January 1, 1994.
</P>
<P>
He said the Zapatista Army of National Liberation (EZLN) in
Chiapas should sit down at the dialogue table to go ahead with the
peaceful process that had been stagnated since talks between the
government and the guerrillas broke down three years ago.
</P>
<P>
He announced a new plan a few days ago to resume negotiations
which he said was very concrete, but the military withdrawal would
not be discussed.
</P>
<P>
Also the Mexican government said it would amnesty some rebels
who are still in jail. 
</P>
