<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Situation in East Timor Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The situation in
violence-torn East Timor was improving, according to reports
reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the Security Restoration Operation Command in East
Timor Maj. Gen. Kiki Syahnakri said, "the situation has not been
fully restored, but it is now much better."
</P>
<P>
Indonesian Military Commander Gen. Wiranto said in Jakarta that
there were no further signs of unrest or the sound of gunfire.
</P>
<P>
"The situation has greatly improved in East Timor, particularly
in Dili (capital of East Timor). I believe the condition will
return to normal in the near future," Wiranto said following a
call on President B.J. Habibie on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government on Tuesday placed East Timor under
martial law following escalating violence after the United Nations
announcement on September 4 that 78.5 percent of voters in the
August 30 direct ballot rejected autonomy under Indonesia, paving
the way for independence.
</P>
<P>
More than a hundred deaths have been reportedly followed the
announcement of the ballot result.
</P>
<P>
In Dili, Chief of the U.N. Mission in East Timor (UNAMET) Ian
Martin said that the security situation has improved but was still
dangerous.
</P>
<P>
"The state of the city is a disgrace, with significant numbers
of (pro-integration) militia members still roaming the streets
with impunity. Dili is a ghost town with not very much left to
loot," Martin was quoted by The Indonesian Observer as saying.
</P>
<P>
U.N. officials said about 40 to 50 U.N. staff, including police
and military liaison officers, will stay behind when another 150
U.N. international workers and 167 local staff members are
evacuated from Dili on Thursday by an Australian air force C-130
transport plane.
</P>
<P>
According to the Antara News Agency, telecommunications,
electricity and water networks in Dili, which were paralyzed in
the past few days following the announcement of the ballot result,
have started functioning again after military personnel repaired
the facilities.
</P>
<P>
The military personnel were busy clearing the debris of
buildings which had been leveled to the ground and repairing
electricity network which had been out of commission since
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
However, Streets and houses in Dili are deserted and economic
activities have yet to resume, with banks and shops being closed.
</P>
<P>
The former Portuguese colony of East Timor was integrated into
Indonesia in 1976 in a move never recognized by the U.N.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia early this year announced it would grant East Timor
independence if the people in the territory reject Indonesia's
offer of a wide-ranging autonomy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
