<HEADLINE> Schroeder Appoints New Transport, Construction Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder Thursday appointed outgoing Minister-President of Saar
State Reinhard Klimmt as the federal government's new transport
and construction minister.
</P>
<P>
Franz Muentefering, former transport and construction minister,
will be named as secretary-general of the Socialist Democratic
Party (SPD) to strengthen the party leadership, Schroeder said.
</P>
<P>
Klimmt, who was just defeated in the state election, told
reporters that he is interested in the new post although he has
been against the financial tightening plan of the federal
government.
</P>
<P>
The 57-year-old, who will go to the new post on September 29,
is the second defeated SPD minister-president appointed as a
federal government official. Schroeder named Hans Eichel, former
minister-president of Hessen State, as the financial minister
succeeding Oskar Lafontaine who resigned suddenly. 
</P>
