<HEADLINE> Myanmar-HK Trade Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Myanmar and
China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) amounted
to 144.36 million U.S. dollars in fiscal 1998-99, up 17.31 percent
from the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The official Economic Indicators said Myanmar's import from the
HKSAR during 1998-99 was valued at 93.64 million dollars, a 50
percent increase over the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar's export to the HKSAR stood at 50.72 million
dollars, down by 16.34 percent.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR also injected 4 million dollars of investment in a
single project into Myanmar in 1998-99.
</P>
<P>
During the five-year period between April 1994 and April 1999,
Myanmar drew investments totaling 69.32 million dollars from the
HKSAR, accounting for 1.2 percent of the total foreign investment
of 5.64 billion dollars it received in 10 projects in the period.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
