<HEADLINE> Panama Improves Anti-Drug Cooperation With US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Panama's new government of
Mireya Moscosos is improving relations and cooperation in the
anti-drug fighting with the United States, said Government and
Justice Minister Winston Spadafora Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spadafora explained that Mosocoso's government, which took over
on September 1, has proposed to strengthen the fight against drug
traffic and money laundering.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government is bettering relations and
cooperation with the United States. "At the same time, we always
keep independent as regards advice, laws and hunting down drug
traffickers," he said.
</P>
<P>
Panama requests the United States' cooperation with the media
and information to be "on time and reliable" in fighting drug
trafficking in his region, Spadafora revealed.
</P>
<P>
Panama also wants to obtain advanced technologies and
instruments against the drug cartels, said Spadafors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
